  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT228-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">kaṭinakar “vēṟupaṭātu naṉku āṟṟiṉāy” eṉak toḻikkuk kiḻatti uraittatu. </p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Told by HER to the confidante who said “you have well
          had the strength not to change in the marriage house”. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT228">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l>vīḻtāḻ tāḻai yūḻuṟu koḻumukai</l>
          <l>kurukuḷa riṟakiṉ viriputō ṭaviḻuṅ</l>
          <l>kāṉa ṉaṇṇiya ciṟukuṭi muṉṟiṟ</l>
          <l>ṟiraivantu peyaru meṉpanat tuṟantu</l>
          <l>neṭuñcē ṇāṭṭā rāyiṉu</l>
          <l>neñciṟ kaṇiyar taṇkaṭa ṉāṭṭē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">

          <l rend="indent3">[To and from] the front-yard of the little home situated</l>
          <l rend="indent9">by the seashore grove,</l>
          <l rend="indent">where, spread out like the quills [which] a heron smooths, the mass</l>
          <l rend="indent">of ripe rich buds open on the Tāḻai trees with hanging aerial roots,</l>
          <l>the waves are coming [and] going <note place="foot">For the <term xml:lang="ta">
            vantu-peyarum </term> construction see KT 212.3, 221.3, 246.4, 321.3, 330.5.</note> ,
            [so] they say,</l>
          <l rend="indent3">to the land of the cool sea of him who is close to [our] heart,</l>
          <l rend="indent5">even if he has abandoned us [and is] in a far away land <note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">nāṭṭār</term> is, in contradistinction to <term xml:lang="ta">nāṭaṉ</term> , not an pronominal noun but a denominative (cf. KT 203.1 <term xml:lang="ta">nāṭṭar</term>
            , 11.7 <term xml:lang="ta">tēettar</term>).</note> .</l>

          <lg type="alternate" sameAs="3,4,6b">
            <l>the waves are coming [and] going, [so] they say,</l>
            <l>near the front-yard of the little home ...</l>
            <l>in the land of the cool sea ...</l>
          </lg>

        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
